{
  "text": "The following growth experiments were conducted in highsalt medium [CITATION_1] containing 250 mM methanol as the substrate and a head space of N 2 /CO 2 (80 : 20). The temperature range for growth was 25-50 u C, with the maximum rate between 40 and 50 u C (see Supplementary Fig. S1a in IJSEM Online). Growth was not observed at 55 u C. Sodium chloride was required for growth, was supported at concentrations of 0.05-1.8 M NaCl and the maximum growth rate occurred at concentrations between 0.2 and 0.6 M NaCl ( Supplementary Fig. S1b in IJSEM Online). Growth was poor with no added MgCl 2 ( Supplementary Fig. S1c ). The optimal conditions for growth were between 10 and \u00a2200 mM MgCl 2 , with the maximum rate between 100 and \u00a2200 mM ( Supplementary Fig. S1c ). Growth was supported between pH 6.0 and 9.0, with the maximum rate between pH 7.0 and 8.0 (Supplementary Fig. S1d ).",
